<seg id=1> The Press Secretary Lamo said: the protestors in "the never extinguishing blaze" should not become the cipher in the algorithm being employed by foreign sources. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Kuala Lumpur) Malaysian Press Secretary Mohamo Lamo said that the protestors in "the never extinguishing blaze" should not become the cipher in any algorithm for the use of foreign money to wreck the country. They should find better ways to express their desires. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> He said that, compared to their violent appeal and making the situation more rough and tumble, the sane approach would be more efficient. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Malaysian Press reports after attending a News Department's family Day activity, Mohamo Lamo said to the reporters that, the government should take measures to allow people to freely express their thoughts. The government may set up 500 "expression centers" in different areas so that citizens can use the proper means to express their opinions and views about the country. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> He said that the government will try to learn and improve to meet people's needs by studying the citizen's opinions and thoughts. </seg>
<seg id=6> He emphasized that this is a democratic country's practice. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> He also urged those protesting to do some serious thinking about the possible aftermath of their demonstrations and actions, since the whole nation has been working very hard to achieve today's prosperity after Malaysia was established 41 years ago. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> He said that the protesters have some support from foreign sources who would like to see a successful revolt against the government, they have not realized that what they did betrayed our country's dignity. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> He expressed that, "If the foreigners come to invest in Malaysia, we welcome you. However, if they pay the protesters, we must object." </seg>
</p>
